    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="720"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">732.56/10–1151</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Brazil</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/> No. 41</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-11">October 11,
                            1951</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State desires to inform the Mission, for its guidance and
                    records, that the second installment amounting to $500,000, due under the terms
                    of Supplement I to the Brazilian Lend-Lease Settlement Arrangement of April 15,
                        1948,<note n="1" xml:id="d720fn1">For text, see <ref
                            target="frus1948v09#pg_383">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1948, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ix</hi>, pp. 383</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1948v09#pg_388">388</ref>.</note> which was signed April 19,
                        1950,<note n="2" xml:id="d720fn2">For information on the supplementary
                        agreement, which applied to certain contingent lend-lease accounts, see
                        editorial note printed in <ref target="frus1950v02#pg_759">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, 1950, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>,
                            p. 759</ref>.</note> has been fully paid in the following manner: <pb
                        facs="1251" n="1229" xml:id="pg_1229"/>
                    <table cols="3" rows="3">
                        <row>
                            <cell>March 15, 1951</cell>
                            <cell role="num">$209,115.41</cell>
                            <cell>from refund credits, accrued on interim arms program contracts,
                                transferred to lease-lend account.</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>October 2, 1951</cell>
                            <cell role="num">1,526.95</cell>
                            <cell>—ditto—</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>October 2, 1951</cell>
                            <cell role="num">289,357.64</cell>
                            <cell>by check from Brazilian Treasury Delegation in New York on the
                                Chase National Bank of New York.</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>After this payment, the balance due under this portion of Brazil’s lend-lease
                    settlement schedule is $1,000,000 payable in two equal installments on or before
                    September 30 of 1952 and 1953.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
